Package: ssfaitk
Type: Package
Title: Small-Scale Fisheries AI Toolkit
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("SSF AI Toolkit Contributors", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "maintainer@example.com")
    )
Description: R interface to the SSF AI Toolkit Python library for analyzing
    small-scale fisheries data. Provides machine learning models for fishing effort
    classification, gear type prediction, and vessel type prediction from GPS tracking
    data. Uses 'reticulate' to interface with the Python package.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.2.0
Depends:
    R (>= 4.0.0)
Imports:
    reticulate (>= 1.35)
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    dplyr,
    ggplot2
VignetteBuilder: knitr
URL: https://github.com/WorldFishCenter/ssf-ai-toolkit
BugReports: https://github.com/WorldFishCenter/ssf-ai-toolkit/issues
Config/reticulate:
  list(
    packages = list(
      list(package = "ssfaitk", pip = TRUE)
    )
  )
